91 // Detect support for r-value references (move semantic).
92 // Move semantic should be enabled with great care in multi-threading environments,
93 // especially if MPFR uses custom memory allocators.
94 // Everything should be thread-safe and support passing ownership over thread boundary.
95 #if (__has_feature(cxx_rvalue_references) || \
96  defined(__GXX_EXPERIMENTAL_CXX0X__) || __cplusplus >= 201103L || \
97  (defined(_MSC_VER) && _MSC_VER >= 1600) && !defined(MPREAL_DISABLE_MOVE_SEMANTIC))
98 
99 #define MPREAL_HAVE_MOVE_SUPPORT
100 
101 // Use fields in mpfr_t structure to check if it was initialized / set dummy initialization
102 #define mpfr_is_initialized(x) (0 != (x)->_mpfr_d)
103 #define mpfr_set_uninitialized(x) ((x)->_mpfr_d = 0 )
104 #endif

597

599  }

601 #ifdef MPREAL_HAVE_MOVE_SUPPORT
602  inline mpreal::mpreal(mpreal&& other)
603  {
604  mpfr_set_uninitialized(mpfr_ptr()); // make sure "other" holds null-pointer (in uninitialized state)
605  mpfr_swap(mpfr_ptr(), other.mpfr_ptr());
606 
607  MPREAL_MSVC_DEBUGVIEW_CODE;
608  }
609 
610  inline mpreal& mpreal::operator=(mpreal&& other)
611  {
612  if (this != &other)
613  {
614  mpfr_swap(mpfr_ptr(), other.mpfr_ptr()); // destructor for "other" will be called just afterwards
615  MPREAL_MSVC_DEBUGVIEW_CODE;
616  }
617  return *this;
618  }
619 #endif

765  // Use SFINAE to restrict arithmetic operations instantiation only for numeric types
766  // This is needed for smooth integration with libraries based on expression templates, like Eigen.
767  // TODO: Do the same for boolean operators.
768  template <typename ArgumentType> struct result_type {};
769 
770  template <> struct result_type<mpreal> {typedef mpreal type;};
771  template <> struct result_type<mpz_t> {typedef mpreal type;};
772  template <> struct result_type<mpq_t> {typedef mpreal type;};
773  template <> struct result_type<long double> {typedef mpreal type;};
774  template <> struct result_type<double> {typedef mpreal type;};
775  template <> struct result_type<unsigned long int> {typedef mpreal type;};
776  template <> struct result_type<unsigned int> {typedef mpreal type;};
777  template <> struct result_type<long int> {typedef mpreal type;};
778  template <> struct result_type<int> {typedef mpreal type;};
779  template <> struct result_type<long long> {typedef mpreal type;};
780  template <> struct result_type<unsigned long long> {typedef mpreal type;};
781  }

930  inline mpreal& mpreal::operator=(const mpreal& v)
931  {
932  if (this != &v)
933  {
934  mp_prec_t tp = mpfr_get_prec( mpfr_srcptr());
935  mp_prec_t vp = mpfr_get_prec(v.mpfr_srcptr());
936 
937  if(tp != vp){
938  clear(mpfr_ptr());
939  mpfr_init2(mpfr_ptr(), vp);
940  }
941 
942  mpfr_set(mpfr_ptr(), v.mpfr_srcptr(), mpreal::get_default_rnd());
943 
944  MPREAL_MSVC_DEBUGVIEW_CODE;
945  }
946  return *this;
947  }

1048  // Use other converters for more precise control on base & precision & rounding:
1049  //
1050  // mpreal(const char* s, mp_prec_t prec, int base, mp_rnd_t mode)
1051  // mpreal(const std::string& s,mp_prec_t prec, int base, mp_rnd_t mode)
1052  //
1053  // Here we assume base = 10 and we use precision of target variable.
1054 
1055  mpfr_t t;
1056 
1057  mpfr_init2(t, mpfr_get_prec(mpfr_srcptr()));
1058 
1059  if(0 == mpfr_set_str(t, s, 10, mpreal::get_default_rnd()))
1060  {
1061  mpfr_set(mpfr_ptr(), t, mpreal::get_default_rnd());
1062  MPREAL_MSVC_DEBUGVIEW_CODE;
1063  }
1064 
1065  clear(t);
1066  return *this;
1067  }

1779  inline std::string mpreal::toString(int n, int b, mp_rnd_t mode) const
1780  {
1781  // TODO: Add extended format specification (f, e, rounding mode) as it done in output operator
1782  (void)b;
1783  (void)mode;
1784 
1785 #if (MPFR_VERSION >= MPFR_VERSION_NUM(2,4,0))
1786 
1787  std::ostringstream format;
1788 
1789  int digits = (n >= 0) ? n : 2 + bits2digits(mpfr_get_prec(mpfr_srcptr()));
1790 
1791  format << "%." << digits << "RNg";
1792 
1793  return toString(format.str());
1794 
1795 #else
1796 
1797  char *s, *ns = NULL;
1798  size_t slen, nslen;
1799  mp_exp_t exp;
1800  std::string out;
1801 
1802  if(mpfr_inf_p(mp))
1803  {
1804  if(mpfr_sgn(mp)>0) return "+Inf";
1805  else return "-Inf";
1806  }
1807 
1808  if(mpfr_zero_p(mp)) return "0";
1809  if(mpfr_nan_p(mp)) return "NaN";
1810 
1811  s = mpfr_get_str(NULL, &exp, b, 0, mp, mode);
1812  ns = mpfr_get_str(NULL, &exp, b, (std::max)(0,n), mp, mode);
1813 
1814  if(s!=NULL && ns!=NULL)
1815  {
1816  slen = strlen(s);
1817  nslen = strlen(ns);
1818  if(nslen<=slen)
1819  {
1820  mpfr_free_str(s);
1821  s = ns;
1822  slen = nslen;
1823  }
1824  else {
1825  mpfr_free_str(ns);
1826  }
1827 
1828  // Make human eye-friendly formatting if possible
1829  if (exp>0 && static_cast<size_t>(exp)<slen)
1830  {
1831  if(s[0]=='-')
1832  {
1833  // Remove zeros starting from right end
1834  char* ptr = s+slen-1;
1835  while (*ptr=='0' && ptr>s+exp) ptr--;
1836 
1837  if(ptr==s+exp) out = std::string(s,exp+1);
1838  else out = std::string(s,exp+1)+'.'+std::string(s+exp+1,ptr-(s+exp+1)+1);
1839 
1840  //out = string(s,exp+1)+'.'+string(s+exp+1);
1841  }
1842  else
1843  {
1844  // Remove zeros starting from right end
1845  char* ptr = s+slen-1;
1846  while (*ptr=='0' && ptr>s+exp-1) ptr--;
1847 
1848  if(ptr==s+exp-1) out = std::string(s,exp);
1849  else out = std::string(s,exp)+'.'+std::string(s+exp,ptr-(s+exp)+1);
1850 
1851  //out = string(s,exp)+'.'+string(s+exp);
1852  }
1853 
1854  }else{ // exp<0 || exp>slen
1855  if(s[0]=='-')
1856  {
1857  // Remove zeros starting from right end
1858  char* ptr = s+slen-1;
1859  while (*ptr=='0' && ptr>s+1) ptr--;
1860 
1861  if(ptr==s+1) out = std::string(s,2);
1862  else out = std::string(s,2)+'.'+std::string(s+2,ptr-(s+2)+1);
1863 
1864  //out = string(s,2)+'.'+string(s+2);
1865  }
1866  else
1867  {
1868  // Remove zeros starting from right end
1869  char* ptr = s+slen-1;
1870  while (*ptr=='0' && ptr>s) ptr--;
1871 
1872  if(ptr==s) out = std::string(s,1);
1873  else out = std::string(s,1)+'.'+std::string(s+1,ptr-(s+1)+1);
1874 
1875  //out = string(s,1)+'.'+string(s+1);
1876  }
1877 
1878  // Make final string
1879  if(--exp)
1880  {
1881  if(exp>0) out += "e+"+mpfr::toString<mp_exp_t>(exp,std::dec);
1882  else out += "e"+mpfr::toString<mp_exp_t>(exp,std::dec);
1883  }
1884  }
1885 
1886  mpfr_free_str(s);
1887  return out;
1888  }else{
1889  return "conversion error!";
1890  }
1891 #endif
1892  }

1898  {

1903  if (os.precision() >= 0)

1907  'g');

1909  format << "R*e";

1911  char *s = NULL;
1912  if(!(mpfr_asprintf(&s, format.str().c_str(),
1913  mpfr::mpreal::get_default_rnd(),
1914  mpfr_srcptr())
1915  < 0))
1916  {
1917  os << std::string(s);
1918  mpfr_free_str(s);
1919  }
1920  return os;

1938  // Bits - decimal digits relation
1939  // bits = ceil(digits*log[2](10))
1940  // digits = floor(bits*log[10](2))
1941 
1942  inline mp_prec_t digits2bits(int d)
1943  {
1944  const double LOG2_10 = 3.3219280948873624;
1945 
1946  return mp_prec_t(std::ceil( d * LOG2_10 ));
1947  }
1948 
1949  inline int bits2digits(mp_prec_t b)
1950  {
1951  const double LOG10_2 = 0.30102999566398119;
1952 
1953  return int(std::floor( b * LOG10_2 ));
1954  }

2073  inline mpreal machine_epsilon(const mpreal& x)
2074  {
2075  /* the smallest eps such that x + eps != x */
2076  if( x < 0)
2077  {
2078  return nextabove(-x) + x;
2079  }else{
2080  return nextabove( x) - x;
2081  }
2082  }

2085  inline mpreal minval(mp_prec_t prec)
2086  {

2092  inline mpreal maxval(mp_prec_t prec)
2093  {
2094  /* max = (1 - eps) * 2^emax, eps is machine epsilon */

2509  inline const mpreal mod (const mpreal& x, const mpreal& y, mp_rnd_t rnd_mode = mpreal::get_default_rnd())
2510  {
2511  (void)rnd_mode;
2512 
2513  /*
2514 
2515  m = mod(x,y) if y != 0, returns x - n*y where n = floor(x/y)
2516 
2517  The following are true by convention:
2518  - mod(x,0) is x
2519  - mod(x,x) is 0
2520  - mod(x,y) for x != y and y != 0 has the same sign as y.
2521 
2522  */
2523 
2524  if(iszero(y)) return x;
2525  if(x == y) return 0;
2526 
2527  mpreal m = x - floor(x / y) * y;
2528 
2529  return copysign(abs(m),y); // make sure result has the same sign as Y
2530  }

2536

2538  xp = x.get_prec();
2539 
2540  a.set_prec(yp>xp?yp:xp);
2541 
2542  mpfr_fmod(a.mp, x.mp, y.mp, rnd_mode);
2543 
2544  return a;
2545  }

2729  // Uniformly distributed random number generation
2730  // a = random(seed); <- initialization & first random number generation
2731  // a = random(); <- next random numbers generation
2732  // seed != 0
2733  inline const mpreal random(unsigned int seed = 0)
2734  {
2735 #if (MPFR_VERSION >= MPFR_VERSION_NUM(3,0,0))
2736  static gmp_randstate_t state;
2737  static bool initialize = true;
2738 
2739  if(initialize)
2740  {
2741  gmp_randinit_default(state);
2742  gmp_randseed_ui(state,0);
2743  initialize = false;
2744  }
2745 
2746  if(seed != 0) gmp_randseed_ui(state,seed);
2747 
2748  return mpfr::urandom(state);
2749 #else
2750  if(seed != 0) std::srand(seed);
2751  return mpfr::mpreal(std::rand()/(double)RAND_MAX);
2752 #endif
2753  }
2754

3113 // Thus standard algorithms will use efficient version of swap (due to Koenig lookup)
3114 // Non-throwing swap C++ idiom: http://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/More_C%2B%2B_Idioms/Non-throwing_swap

3117  inline const mpfr::mpreal& min(const mpfr::mpreal& a, const mpfr::mpreal& b, bool omitnan = false)
3118  {
3119  if(omitnan)
3120  {
3121  if(isnan(a)) return b;
3122  else if(isnan(b)) return a;
3123  }
3124  else
3125  {
3126  if(isnan(a)) return a;
3127  else if(isnan(b)) return b;
3128  }
3129 
3130  return a <= b ? a : b;
3131  }
3132

3142  if(isnan(a)) return a;
